@node "About" "About"
@prev "Main"
@next "Copyright"

 @{b}xDiz@{ub} is a FILE_ID.DIZ adder/viewer/stripper/extractor for @{b}xpk@{ub}-packed files


The  sense of this program is to keep the file descriptions in the file and
NOT   in   a  seperate  file.   Originally  it  was  developed  for trading
xpk-packed modules,  but there's no limitation; any file that is xpk-packed
can  be  treated  with  xDiz.   So  it's  very  useful to keep informations
about the file  IN  the file, e.g.  the production, the name of the author,
the playing  time  or  the  style.  You  can  also  use  it for  xpk-packed
exe-files (description of the demo/intro etc.) or for xpk-packed whatevers.
There should not be any problem with unpacking the files as the description
is stored behind the xpk-file which then will just be ignored.

You can also use it for stripping everything that doesn't belong to the xpk
file (e.g. you ripped an xpk-file and want to strip it to the right length).
@endnode


